result.name: Nan Tei Happy Valley

reviews.text: Great food, fast service, just watch out for the “$23HK” vegetables on your table. You will be charged for them! Don’t take them.
Still love coming here! A favourite for HKgers and gets quite crowded at peak hours. Really can't beat a night out with your best buddy over some cold sake and chicken wings. Life is good!

Name changed because of split. Nan Tei is still the pioneer of robatayaki restaurants in Hong Kong with a history measured by decades. Among all branches, Happy Valley is still my favaorite for its “secluded coziness”.  Advanced booking is highly recommended unless you're super lucky.

Love their food since their very first shop in central. Going to this shop now because plenty of parking spaces nearby, service is also as good as other shops. Price may be a little bit above average but well-worth it. Excellent place for small group or people who wanna chat over a few drinks and some really good skewers!
The service was incredibly slow and we had to remind them about our dishes. The restaurant was only half full so wouldn't want to try when it's busy. The food was tasty but not good value for money
